.TH CLAMDSCAN-WATCH 1 "March 2026" "clamdscan-tools 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clamdscan-watch \- display or follow clamdscan-tools logs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clamdscan-watch
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clamdscan-watch
shows the most recent log produced by
.BR clamdscan-progress (1)
or a specific log file chosen with
.BR --log .
It can also follow the file with
.BR tail -f .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --log " FILE"
Display the given log file instead of auto-detecting the latest one.
.TP
.BR --follow ", " -f
Keep following the selected log file.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show the built-in help text and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/clamdscan-tools/clamdscan-tools.conf
Provides the log directory used for auto-detection.
.TP
.I /var/log/clamdscan-tools/
Default location of generated scan logs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The command exits with status 0 on success, 1 when no readable log is found and
2 on invalid command line usage.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show the latest log:
.B clamdscan-watch
.TP
Follow the latest log:
.B clamdscan-watch --follow
.TP
Open a specific log:
.B clamdscan-watch --log /var/log/clamdscan-tools/scan_2026-03-23_12-00-00.log
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clamdscan-progress (1),
.BR tail (1),
.BR info (1)
